cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD

This paper is about natural language generation from owl ontologies, which involves natural language processing and artificial intelligence techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of linguistic resources and the evaluation of the system, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper also touches on the accessibility of information to end-users, which could relate to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
